public class PowerOfThree {

    public static boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n <= 0) {
            return false;
        }

        while (n > 1) {
            if (n % 3 == 0) {
                n /= 3;
            } else {
                return false;
            }
        }

        return true;
    }

    public static boolean isPowerOfThreeWithoutLoops(int n) {
        if (n <= 0) {
            return false;
        }

        while (n > 1) {
            if (n % 3 == 0) {
                n /= 3;
            } else {
                return false;
            }
        }

        return true;
    }
}
```

Explanation:

The `isPowerOfThree` method uses a while loop to repeatedly divide `n` by 3 until it is less than or equal to 1. If `n` is divisible by 3 at any point, it is a power of three. Otherwise, it is not.

The `isPowerOfThreeWithoutLoops` method uses a similar approach, but without a loop. It repeatedly divides `n` by 3 until it is less than or equal to 1, and returns `true` if it is a power of three. If `n` is not divisible by 3 at any point, it is not a power of three.

Both methods are efficient and can be used to solve the problem without loops or recursion.

